QATAR BIOBANK
RESEARCH OFFICE
RESEARCH PROPOSAL SUBMISSION FORM (FB- IRB)

components.label: Title of the project
components.tooltip: Please provide the project title - limit: 1000 characters including spaces and punctuations
please clarify all the list of investigators involved in this research proposal, and their roles in the research
components.label: Research Team Members & Roles
3. Address for Correspondence
components.description: Name, Department, Section, Mobile Telephone, Email, Address, Lead PI
components.tooltip: up to 2 responsible members of the research team

components.label: 4. Background
components.description: Organize your background into introduction, literature review with numbered references, research question(s), hypothesis (if any), rationale and Justification) 500 words.
components.tooltip: Description of the study stating the problem and its public health importance

components.label: 5.a. Goal(s) of the study
components.description: State the focus of your research as concisely as possible, preferably numbered points

components.label: 5.b. Primary Objective(s)
components.description: (State the main overall objective(s) of your research) Maximum 3

components.legend: 6. Facilities to be used during the project:
components.tooltip: List all facilities included in this project in this section
components.label: 5. Aim(s) of the study
6.a.
components.description: please identify and specify any named Health Center(s)  included in this project

components.label: 6.b. Time (When will the study be conducted?):
components.description: (e.g. Is it during working hours or shift?) One sentence.

components.tooltip: Describe the research methods chosen for the study in this section
components.label: Materials and Methods
7.a. Study Subjects
components.tooltip: Specify characteristics that describe your study population in the following sections

components.label: 7.a.1. What are the inclusion criteria for the study?
components.description: Please list all the inclusion criteria

components.label: 7.a.2. What are the exclusion criteria for the study?
components.description: Please list all the exclusion criteria

components.label: 7.b. Study Design
components.description: (Mention the type of study design to be employed e.g. Is it experimental or observational; randomized; who are the subjects, groups etc.?) 150 words.

components.label: 7.c. Sample Size
components.description: (Mention the input criteria for sample size estimation like existing prevalence rates, previous study data, pilot study results etc. and demonstrate how sample size was calculated)

components.label: 7.d. Sampling Technique
components.description: Please describe the sampling type(s)(e.g. probability and/or non-probability) and technique(s) that will be used in the study.  150 words.

components.label: Are any of the following involved?(please indicate YES, NO or NA)

questions.label: Intrusive procedure(s)( e.g. questionnaire, interview, focus group, participant log or diary)
Covert observation or covert filming/ recording
Invasive procedure(s) ( e.g. venipuncture, tissue sampling)
Drugs, medical products or medical devices
Working with sources of ionizing radiation

components.label: 7.e.1. Describe the instruments used for data collection
components.description: (Questionnaire, survey forms, sphygmomanometer, stethoscope etc.) 150 words.

components.label: 7.e.2. Procedure(s) of data collection
components.description: (please describe in detail, mentioning e.g. who will be collecting the data, how prospective participants will be recruited, where the interaction with participants will take place, the expected duration of participation in the study for each participant and the process of data collection) 150 words.

components.label: 7.e.3. Types of Outcome Measurements
components.description: (List the primary and secondary outcome measurements for the study) Maximum 5

components.label: 7.e.4. Describe the quality control measures ationd good practices to be followed during the study
components.description: (E.g. Methods used to make sure that data collected is accurate, reliable, valid, compliant with the research protocol, data safety monitoring plan etc.) 150 words.

components.label: 8. Possible implications of study results for health improvement
components.description: (E.g. for clinical, public health or service improvements etc.) 150 words.

components.label: 9. Bibliographic References
components.description: (Provide a full citation of all articles mentioned in your protocol)

components.label: 10.a. List all possible ethical issues related to the study
components.description: E.g. Privacy, anonymity and data protection

components.label: 10.b. For each ethical issue identified, state how they will be addressed
components.description: E.g. For privacy private space will be provided for all consultations

components.label: 10.c. From whom and how will consent be obtained?
components.description: (Participant or legally authorized representative. In the case of retrospective anonymized data collection e.g. from medical records, indicate how permission will be obtained from the Research Section) 100 words.

components.label: 10.d. Confidentiality
components.description: (How and where will the study data be stored and secured and how will subject’s confidentiality be protected? Who will have access to confidential research information etc.)100 words.

components.label: 10.e. Vulnerable population as research participants (if applicable)

values.label: Pregnant women or those with young infants

components.label: 10.f. Describe the measures that you will take to protect any vulnerable populations in your study.
components.description: (100 words)

components.label: Conflict of interest
components.description: (if you have any conflict of interest, please fill up the form “conflict of interest”)

components.legend: 12. Contact information in case of queries about the Research:
components.tooltip: details of whom the research participant must contact in case of questions or doubts
components.label: Field Set
13. Strategies to enhance the dissemination and utilization of results
components.description: List the measures that might be taken to make research findings available to others. e.g. workshop, presentations or conference, local publication, peer reviewed publications

components.label: 14. Study Duration
components.description: please specify the proposed start and end dates for the project

components.label: 15. Timelines
components.description: Please indicate the activities to be conducted and mark(X) in the corresponding month on the Gantt chart.

components.tooltip: Describe the type and funding source for your project
components.label: Budget
16.b. If a budget is required specify
Name of the extramural funding agency

components.html:
I hereby acknowledge, by my signature below, that I must adhere to the applicable laws & standards stipulated in the Qatar Supreme Council of Health: Ethical Principles Policies, Regulations and Guidelines for Research Involving Human Subject and to protect the rights and welfare of human subjects involved in this research conducted under this Agreement.

I understand that any subject’s information to which I have access is considered confidential and my obligation to safeguard confidentiality continues during and after my termination of the project.

Subject Confidential Information includes:

All medical records, paper, electronic data, diagnostic & therapeutic reports, medical history, subject’s treatment and/or their family members’ records.

 

Under this Agreement I will report promptly to the Research section any proposed changes in the research protocols, any unanticipated problems involving risks to subjects or others.

I admit and agree to cooperate in the Research section’s responsibility for continuing review, record keeping, and reporting. I will provide all information requested by the Research section in a timely fashion.

I have read and understand the foregoing information and that my signature below signifies my agreement to comply with the above terms
